Description: Fragment of oval handle of a Rhodian pottery transport amphora at neck join. Deeply stamped. Clay near fine red-brown. Triangular stamp.
Curator's comments: Petrie Diary 1884-5 (EES Archive XVII 47) p. 173, 24, 31, 16 or 31,50. Perhaps from same die as a piece from Kaunos, B.Schmaltz, Die Hellenistischen Amphorenstempel vom Kaunos (Asia Minor Studien 79) 91, KA 216.
Bibliographic references: Villing et al 2013-2015 / Naukratis: Greeks in Egypt (JB.1548)
